checked in an order-agnostic manner.

commit.message:
Fix random testNoGroupLoader failures caused by test ordering

Changes in JUnit and Java itself have caused the test ordering to
change since these tests were first written. The testNoGroupLoader is
sensitive to this but always passes if placed at the start of the run
so make use of JUnit 4.11's FixMethodOrder feature.

In order to more neatly separate the JUnit tests from the product source code
and ensure that projects open by Maven IDE plugins (Netbeans, IntelliJ, Eclipse)
can track the source code more accurately, the unit test for string template are now
relocated into their own tree 'test', which exists at the same level as the 'src' tree.

The pom.xml project definition is changed accordingly.
